Premaxilla with two tooth rows; outer row with 2-4, tricuspid or pentacuspid teeth with central cusp longer; inner row 5 (one with 4) teeth with 5-7 cusps and central cusp longer and broader than other cusps, inner row teeth gradually decreasing in length from first to fourth teeth, last tooth considerably smaller. Two to three maxillary teeth, with 5 cusps, central cusp slightly longer. Four or 5 anteriormost dentary teeth larger, with 5-7 cusps, followed by medium sized tooth with 5 cusps, and 5-6 smaller teeth with 1-3 cusps or conical; central cusp in all teeth two to three times longer and broader than remaining cusps. Cusp tips slightly curved posteriorly and lingually (
Fig. 2
).
